- Candidate 1 (Carefully sequenced anthology…): Strengths: clarified low end and remastering that restores punch and crystalline detail match my demand for muscular lows and transient snap. Tasteful sequencing and revealed tactile instrument tone are positives. Weaknesses relative to my dislikes: it explicitly emphasizes generous room ambience, spacious front‑to‑back imaging, minimal vocal processing and immersive layered listening—features that typically push vocals back into the room, increase perceived distance, and can dilute immediate groove and hook focus. That ambience/front‑to‑back staging risks burying pocket and reducing the punchy, radio‑forward lead placement I prefer.
