- The Beach Boys compilation offers superb stacked, multi‑tracked harmonies and a low‑compression remaster preserving micro‑dynamics (both positive for my “crystalline harmonies” and headroom preferences). However, it emphasizes dense close‑mic multitracked overdubs and front‑center harmony mixes with a generally restrained low end. That dense, harmony‑first presentation can reduce instrument separation and tends to center the vocal mass as a blended texture rather than foregrounding a single, natural mid‑range lead. I also want punchy, transient drums and a more elastic low end; the Beach Boys description stresses restrained lows and a harmony‑first balance rather than the tight, muscular low‑mid control and lead immediacy I favor.
